To rape (a woman); later more generally, to sexually abuse (someone).
To abuse verbally, to insult.
To become a friend of, to make friends with.
To act as a friend to, to assist.
To favor.
Capable of giving out a deep, resonant sound.
definitions.example: The highlight of the hike was the sonorous cave, which produced a ringing echo from the hiker’s shouts.

definitions.definition: Full of sound and rich, as in language or verse.
definitions.example: He was selected to give the opening speech thanks to his imposing, sonorous voice.

definitions.definition: Wordy or grandiloquent.
Produced with a relatively open vocal tract and relatively little obstruction of airflow.
